Methods in StateMachine with parameters of type Command
 void StateMachine.execute(Command c)
          Executes a Command c on the DFA, meaning that it tries to go from StateMachine.state with c to another State, if that is not possible (because StateMachine.state has no edge for the Command c) it throws a StateException.
(package private)  State State.execute(Command c)
          Checks if the Command c is a key in State.neighbors, if it is, the State it refers to is returned.
